      <div resp="part:emfr" type="translation">
        <p n="1">
         		Twentieth year of the victorious king Mahendravarman<note>Macīntiraparumaṉ in the original Tamil text.</note>.
         	</p>
        <p n="2-3">
         		<supplied reason="subaudible">This is the</supplied> stone of Vīravar<note>That is, "the heroic one".</note>, the son <supplied reason="subaudible">of</supplied> Pālācirikar, ruler of Ciṟuppāl, <supplied reason="subaudible">who fell</supplied> at the time of seizing cattle <supplied reason="subaudible">in/of</supplied> Kaṭṭaiyūr in Mīvēṇṇāṭu.</p>
      </div>
      <div type="commentary">
        <p>
         		Line beginnings not indicated in <bibl>
            <ptr target="bib:Kalvettu"/>
          </bibl>, here after <bibl>
            <ptr target="bib:Dayalan2005_01"/>
          </bibl>.
         	</p>
        <p>
         		Pālācirikar, ruler of Ciṟuppāl = Pālāyiriyar, ruler of Ciṟuppāl (INSPallava407) = Pālācirir, the ruler of Ciṟuppāḻ (INSPallava409).
         	</p>
      </div>
